diff:1670645036:1669429868:=53,70c53%0a%3c #foxbegin 221210-040356-948980#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Interesting factoids about Wenzhounese %0a%3c -> - tiagocecchi1216%0a%3c -> [-09.12.2022 - 20:03-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221210-040356-948980 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c Note that Wenzhounese is widely spoken in overseas Chinese communities. These include Brooklyn’s Chinatown as well as the Chinese community in Flushing, Queens. Europe also has a large Wenzhounese-speaking population, in particular Italy, where Wenzhounese is actually more widely spoken.%0a%3c %0a%3c Wenzhounese, like Manchu, also retains the yin-yang distinction. That is, vowels are divided into two categories; yin, or femenine objects are categorized by front vowels, and yang, or masculine objects that are categorized by back vowels. That is, changing the vowel of a word also changes its gender. Wenzhounese has eight phonetic tones, of which the rù tone is of the greatest interest. This tone differs from its counterparts in other dialects in that it has lost its final stop but also lengthened its vowel and generally the tone has become more complex.%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221210-040356-948980#%0a---%0a> %0a
